en_1818820_0	The authorities in Dubai are trying to find out what caused a spectacular fire to engulf a 63-storey luxury hotel in the city centre on New Year’s Eve.
en_1818820_1	Firefighters managed to subdue the blaze, but part of the Address Downtown Hotel is still smouldering.
en_1818820_2	The tower was evacuated and 16 people were hurt.
en_1818820_3	But a fireworks show went ahead at the Burj Khalifa tower nearby.
en_1818820_4	The Burj Khalifa is the world’s tallest building and an iconic symbol of the United Arab Emirates (UAE). -BBC
